                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1593">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/95.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">German Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Imperial German Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Newport</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-04T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 4, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>By order of the Imperial Government I have the honor to pray your excellency most
                    kindly to arrange that the protection of German life and property in the
                    Republic of Mexico be formally assumed by the American land forces and war
                    vessels.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Von Haniel</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
